<a href="javascript:card_browser(217)">Council Courtyard</a><br>
Eregion Hills<br>
Bridge<br>
Forests of Lothlorien<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(234)">Silverlode Banks</a> (or w<a href="javascript:card_browser(140)">Hate</a>ver is the no ranger=shot site)<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(238)">Shores of Nen Hithoel</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(240)">Emyn Muil</a><br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> First of all, yes this deck is huge.  It DOES go through it though, with three elronds, ottar, and gandalf.  Most free peoples cards you can play immediately, such as citadels or gondor bowmen.  If you can fit a shards in, it would be nice to stack extra copies of Aragorn, horns, etc. on.  So dont slam this deck saying it is way to big, because it does work.  You wont run out of cards, rather you will have 5-10 left at the end.(pretty good for an 80 card non moria deck).  The deck generally wins by reaching site nine alive, but it can also pull off an overwhelmed frodo with 4 enduring evils and desperate defense/gleaming in the snow to fuel them.<br>
<br>
Free Peoples:  Bid 2 to 3.  Going first isnt a win/lose situation, but it is nice to go first.  Pippin will remove one, and that will generally be added back with the pony.  Play Aragorn always, as he heals everyone, and can launch the bowmen(along with boro).  WATCH YOUR TWILIGHT ON FIRST TURN).  Some times you will get lego, gandalf, and rond in hand.  If you play them all immedialtely, the Uruks will give you a night to remember! Site 2 against uruks is not this decks finest hour...so play accordingly.  If you can, go to site 3 on first turn.  Discard anything that is not IMMEDIATELY available.  You have to clear your hand out with this deck.  Move to site 4, and plan/shoot accordingly so that you can win all your skirmishes if possible.  If you wont face the balrog at site 5, you can push your luck and hope to win them all again at site 5.  This is not done by power, but rather by calling in power 11/14 rond, and unleashing massive shots.  The healing from citadel will ease your double moving.  By site nine, it is good to amass at least 2 gondor bowmen, and a fully healed legolas with his banner.  A lot of times, you can dish out 6-9 shots at the last site if you prepare.  This storming of the adventure path is how the deck wins most often.<br>
<br>
Shadow:  Scares your opponent and makes him stop.  Who would move on a morgul hunter with a vile blade, and the threat of an enduring evil?  Several subtle touches also.  The pony can tempt the opponent to add a burden even if they dont normally start the pony.  The eregion hills also will add a burden, albeit you might not be using your path.  Desperate defense/gleaming in the snow will also add.  Remeber you only need 2 or 3 burdens to overwhelm.  Play your minions strategically - 2 orc ambushers w/ enduring evil can often win a game.  And orc swordsmen with a vile blade is power 15 for 4 twightlight against a man or elf.  Most of the time you wont kill your opponent with this before site nine, but with your movement patterns, they will have to double into nine to beat you.  If they do this, you can cause some major death with emyn muil.  A tricky technique (if no sting) is to save up 3 or 4 enduring evils.  Garunteed dead frodo if he fights. So mainly, the shadow side will stop, not brutalize (like uruks).  It can rise to the challenge though.<br>
<br>
Sites: <br>
1-aragorn, can make opponent add a burden<br>
2-not too useful for oppoenent(unless twighlight nazgul), and adds enought for your minions.<br>
3-alot of times they will reach 3 before you, playing your site.  When you get here, alot of times you will add tons of twighlight.  Can protect against hollin.<br>
4-burden<br>
5-??? i dunno<br>
6-Celeborn<br>
7-we want archery<br>
8-stop them if you wish, or serve them on a dish<br>
9-fierce mourgul hunters anyone? </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25666"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25666" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
